# Plugin Frontend Architecture

React 19 + Valtio + Tailwind CSS 4. Runs in Figma iframe. Data from plugin backend only via broker.

## Structure

```
frontend/
├── components/
│   ├── layout/     # header, footer
│   ├── screens/    # mcp, websocket, session, about, mini, error, warning
│   ├── ui/         # shared primitives (button, input, tab, etc.)
│   └── utils/      # fit-container, history-navigator, validation-message
├── hooks/          # use-routing-status, use-valid-url, use-smooth-scroll
├── stores/         # Valtio stores (session, endpoints)
└── lib/            # tv, frontend-broker, copy, ws-manager (WebSocket lifecycle)
```

Do not create `features/`, `utils/`, or `helpers/` — use existing folders. One name per responsibility.

## Valtio pattern

- Stores: `proxy()` in `stores/*.ts`. Subscribe to broker events, mutate store directly.
- Components: read via `useSnapshot(store)` — never import store and mutate from components.
- Expose a hook per store: `useSession()`, `useEndpoints()` — ensures broker listener is set up.

## Broker pattern

- Data from plugin backend **only** via `frontendBroker.on(event, callback)`.
- Send to backend via `frontendBroker.post(event, data)`.
- No direct `figma.*` or `window.parent.postMessage` in components — use the broker.

## WebSocket

The WebSocket to PartyKit lives in the frontend only (backend cannot create sockets). Use `lib/ws-manager.ts` to create, send, and close the connection. Components call `wsManager.close()` for disconnect — do not post disconnect events to the backend.

## Styling (Tailwind Variants)

- Use `tv()` from `lib/tv.ts` for component variants — not inline class concatenation.
- Custom tokens: `text-title`, `text-body`, `text-caption`, `text-label` (from @theme).

## TypeScript

- `strict: true`. No `any`. Use `unknown` and narrow.
- Props: explicit interface. Types used in 2+ files → `types.ts` in nearest scope.
- Prefer `type` for shapes; `interface` for extensible contracts.

## Naming

- Components: PascalCase. Hooks: `use` prefix. Files: kebab-case.
- Event handlers: `handle` prefix. Booleans: `is`, `has`, `can` prefix.

## Rules

- Handle loading, error, empty states — not just happy path.
- Prefer declarative (`map`, `filter`, `reduce`) over imperative loops.
- Do not add `utils/` or `helpers/` when `lib/` exists.
- Do not use magic strings — constants or enums.
